posts.name: Fletch
posts.cooked:
Has the navx library been updated for 2023 yet? Last I heard (a couple hours ago) it hadn’t.  If not, that’s almost 100% certain to be your problem.  Not a bug, just an unsupported version.

Ninjedit: Doesn’t look like it.  Latest comment here was 1/2022. RoboRIO Libraries | navX-MXP

posts.name: Brian Z
posts.cooked: We are having the same issue currently while trying to implement field orientation on our new drive base. The gen2 repo is private due to some bad actors attempting to steal designs or something like that if you want access to the gen2 repo you have to sign an NDA. Just a waiting game at this point, unfortunately.
